# Next.js Data Handling Patterns

Enforce strict separation of data concerns and validation patterns in Next.js applications.

## Data Retrieval: Server Components Only

All data fetching must happen in Server Components. Never fetch data in Client Components.

### ✅ GOOD - Server Component Data Fetching
```typescript
// app/dashboard/page.tsx
import { auth } from '@clerk/nextjs';
import { db } from '@/db';
import { decks } from '@/db/schema';
import { eq } from 'drizzle-orm';

export default async function DashboardPage() {
  const { userId } = auth();
  if (!userId) redirect('/sign-in');

  // Fetch data in Server Component
  const userDecks = await db.select()
    .from(decks)
    .where(eq(decks.userId, userId));

  return (
    <div>
      {userDecks.map(deck => <DeckCard key={deck.id} deck={deck} />)}
    </div>
  );
}
```

### ❌ BAD - Client Component Data Fetching
```typescript
// DON'T fetch data in Client Components
'use client';
import { useEffect, useState } from 'react';

export default function DashboardPage() {
  const [decks, setDecks] = useState([]);
  
  useEffect(() => {
    fetch('/api/decks').then(r => r.json()).then(setDecks); // ❌ BAD
  }, []);
}
```

## Data Mutations: Server Actions Only

All database writes (INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE) must use Server Actions with proper validation.

### ✅ GOOD - Server Action with Zod Validation
```typescript
// app/dashboard/actions.ts
'use server';
import { auth } from '@clerk/nextjs';
import { revalidatePath } from 'next/cache';
import { z } from 'zod';
import { db } from '@/db';
import { decks } from '@/db/schema';

const CreateDeckSchema = z.object({
  title: z.string().min(1).max(100),
  description: z.string().max(500).optional(),
});

type CreateDeckInput = z.infer<typeof CreateDeckSchema>;

export async function createDeck(data: CreateDeckInput) {
  const { userId } = auth();
  if (!userId) throw new Error('Unauthorized');

  // Validate with Zod
  const validatedData = CreateDeckSchema.parse(data);

  const [newDeck] = await db.insert(decks)
    .values({
      ...validatedData,
      userId,
    })
    .returning();

  revalidatePath('/dashboard');
  return { success: true, deck: newDeck };
}
```

### ❌ BAD - Using FormData Type
```typescript
// ❌ DON'T use FormData as the type
export async function createDeck(formData: FormData) {
  const title = formData.get('title') as string; // No validation
  // ...
}
```

### ❌ BAD - API Route for Mutations
```typescript
// ❌ DON'T use API routes for database mutations
// app/api/decks/route.ts
export async function POST(request: Request) {
  // Use Server Actions instead
}
```

## Zod Validation Requirements

All data inputs must be validated using Zod schemas with proper TypeScript types.

### ✅ GOOD - Comprehensive Zod Schema
```typescript
import { z } from 'zod';

const UpdateCardSchema = z.object({
  id: z.string().uuid(),
  front: z.string().min(1, 'Front is required').max(1000),
  back: z.string().min(1, 'Back is required').max(1000),
  difficulty: z.enum(['easy', 'medium', 'hard']).optional(),
});

type UpdateCardInput = z.infer<typeof UpdateCardSchema>;

export async function updateCard(data: UpdateCardInput) {
  const { userId } = auth();
  if (!userId) throw new Error('Unauthorized');

  const validatedData = UpdateCardSchema.parse(data);
  
  // Verify ownership before update
  const [existingCard] = await db.select()
    .from(cards)
    .innerJoin(decks, eq(cards.deckId, decks.id))
    .where(and(eq(cards.id, validatedData.id), eq(decks.userId, userId)));

  if (!existingCard) throw new Error('Card not found');

  const [updatedCard] = await db.update(cards)
    .set({
      front: validatedData.front,
      back: validatedData.back,
      difficulty: validatedData.difficulty,
      updatedAt: new Date(),
    })
    .where(eq(cards.id, validatedData.id))
    .returning();

  revalidatePath('/dashboard');
  return { success: true, card: updatedCard };
}
```

### ❌ BAD - No Validation
```typescript
// ❌ DON'T skip validation
export async function updateCard(data: any) {
  // Direct database access without validation
  await db.update(cards).set(data);
}
```

## Client-Server Communication

Client Components must call Server Actions with validated data.

### ✅ GOOD - Client Component Using Server Action
```typescript
'use client';
import { createDeck } from './actions';
import { useState } from 'react';

export function CreateDeckForm() {
  const [isSubmitting, setIsSubmitting] = useState(false);

  async function handleSubmit(event: FormEvent<HTMLFormElement>) {
    event.preventDefault();
    setIsSubmitting(true);

    const formData = new FormData(event.currentTarget);
    const data = {
      title: formData.get('title') as string,
      description: formData.get('description') as string,
    };

    try {
      await createDeck(data); // Typed data, not FormData
      // Handle success
    } catch (error) {
      // Handle validation or server errors
    } finally {
      setIsSubmitting(false);
    }
  }

  return (
    <form onSubmit={handleSubmit}>
      <input name="title" required />
      <textarea name="description" />
      <button type="submit" disabled={isSubmitting}>
        Create Deck
      </button>
    </form>
  );
}
```

## Summary Checklist

- [ ] Data fetching only in Server Components
- [ ] Database mutations only via Server Actions
- [ ] All inputs validated with Zod schemas
- [ ] TypeScript types for Server Action parameters (not FormData)
- [ ] User authentication checked in all Server Actions
- [ ] Proper error handling with validation feedback
- [ ] `revalidatePath()` called after mutations